{
  "texts": [
    "The DP algorithm, which takes advantage of data-driven off-line training, achieved better performance in all three metrics, making it suitable for tracking predefined biogas production targets for a short period of time.",
    "To improve the resilience of biogas production over a longer period, a policy mirror descent (PMD) 39 based RL algorithm is applied.",
    "PMD is a general class of policy gradient methods to offer state-of-the-art total sample complexity for RL problems by separately handling the bias and expected error of the gradient, which allows one to decrease the bias more quickly.",
    "A smaller bias leads to more accurate solutions when the gradient is unknown, as is the case in non-linear dynamic systems such as the AD process.",
    "In addition to the feed mixing problem stated in Section ''Variable production control'', we also consider the inventory control problem for separate storage tanks of FW, AW, and MSW under the disturbances in feed supply."
  ]
}